Implement Go-native tool permission system with runtime callback support.
Enables dynamic permission decisions, input modification, and rule updates.

Key features:
- PermissionResult interface with Allow/Deny implementations
- PermissionManager interface for callback management
- ToolPermissionContext for CLI context and suggestions
- Timeout-protected callback execution (5 seconds)
- Panic recovery and error handling
- Support for input modification and permission updates

Permission capabilities:
- Dynamic allow/deny decisions for tool execution
- Input modification before tool execution
- Permission rule updates (add/replace/remove)
- Permission mode switching (session/user/project/local)
- Conversation interruption on denial

Use cases:
- Block dangerous commands (rm -rf, etc.)
- Redirect file writes to safe directories
- Add safety checks to bash commands
- Enforce organizational policies
- Log and audit tool usage

Thread-safe implementation with proper resource cleanup and
graceful fallback to allow when no callback is set.

